I think this is the right place to post this… if its not sorry.
I am part of an older team with not many new parts, so I was going to use some of the better motor controllers that we had (The TalonSRX) for the drive train. when they were not working I looked into the FRC2021 docs and found that they were no longer supported by FRC and you had to download a 3rd party software. If somebody could inform me on what software to download and how to do it that would be great!

Here is a good place to start.

docs.ctre-phoenix.com

Prepare your workstation computer

Before Installing Phoenix…: It is strongly recommended to complete the base installation of FRC tools. https://docs.wpilib.org/en/latest/docs/getting-started/getting-started-frc-control-system/cont...

You should get a Phoenix release and follow the offline installation for both it and then the phoenix library (post-steps). I think right now the online installer will put the wrong version you’d want, but after kickoff that is another way to get the library. Then you can learn how to use the library using the docs or examples.

edit: To offline install the library, follow in here adding offline libraries: 3rd Party Libraries — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation

Do you have a pigeon attached to a TalonSRX? If so make sure you create the pigeon with a TalonSRX as a parameter instead of a CAN ID. I had the issue when I was identifying my pigeon by CAN instead of creating the Talon

Do this

    private final TalonSRX pigeonTalon = new TalonSRX(PIGEON_ID);
    private final PigeonIMU m_pigeon = new PigeonIMU(pigeonTalon);

Not This

    private final PigeonIMU m_pigeon = new PigeonIMU(PIGEON_ID);
